<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99737561596434></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99737561596434><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=1&mid=99737561596434>RE: A good way to level up for large warriors</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 9th 12:46 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree the weighted axe is a great weapon for pulling.  I looted mine shortly after movning to FM to hunt at the giant fort.  I would slam the mob, to make sure I could hit it, and then attack with the weighted axe.  Run back to the group. Waite for the mob to hit me and the attack with the axe again.  Tipical it took longer than the weapons delay to get back to the group.  I would then switch weapons.  <br>With dubble attacks and  a lot of damage.  It was not uncommon for the mob to take between 200 hps to 400 hps of damage pulling this way.  I continued to use the weighted axe while hunting in OT.  My best critical 281 :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
