<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99729171565921></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99729171565921><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=1&mid=99729171565921>Warrior 202 (weapons)</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 8th 1:28 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It has been said that the most important thing a warrior does in a group is to keep the mob off of healers and nukers.  Almost with out exception the mob will attack whoever has done the most damage over a peirod of time.  Thus the most important factor on choosing a weapon or weapon is how much damage it does in X amount of time.  This number can be calculated by ((100)(weapon damage))/by weapon delay.  The weapon's "ratio" show on this borad is related to the inverse of this number. <br>According to the data I have looked at the off hand weapon accounts for 40% of the attack attempts.  You can therefore calculate a combined damage out put for a duel wield combo by timing the damage of the off hand weapon by 0.667 and adding it to the damage of the primary weapon and plugging it into the equation above, where the delay is that of the primary weapon.  Note this assume that the off hand weapon is faster.  <br><br>Using the above you can calculate a damage rate for dual weilded weapons that can be compaired to a damage rate for Two hand weapons. Which ever has the higher damage rate is the one you should use.  You will of course want to keep as many weapon skill max as possible.  <br><br>Another common concern is how much damage do I need to be doing at my lvl.  Based on several factors I have developed the following.  <br>Lvl 1-9 damage rate 10 or better<br>Lvl 10-19 20 or better<br>Lvl 20-29 30 or better<br>Lvl 30-39 40 or better<br>Lvl 40-49 50 or better<br>Lvl 50+   60 or better<br>Required weapon and suggested weapon. The suggestion are for nontwinks, and for the most part can be obtain by looting.  <br><br>lvl 1-9 rusty short sword, Short Sword (DR 16.7). the SS can be bought for about 20gp at vendors.  Note you should use only 1hs for the first 10 lvl to get all your melee skill up.<br><br>lvl 10-19 Dual wield:  SS&SS (DR 27.8), Fine steel long swords (DR 35.7). Two handed:  FS two handed sword (DR 27.9)  FS weapon drop in a number of zone, at this lvl you will need to buy them.  <br><br>lvl 20-29 Dual wield: FSLS&FSLS (DR 35.7), Langseaxes (DR 43.5) Two handed: Langseax of the Wolves (DR 43.2) Notice the nice agreeance in obtainable damage rate from the same quest.  <br><br>Another common question is: Is this weapon I'm considering buying better enough that the one I have to justify the cost?  This one you will have to figure out by yourself, all I can say that an increases of 2 in the damage rate makes a noticable differance in damage.  <br><br>Live Large <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
